ENTRY       EC 6.2.1.35                 Enzyme
NAME        ACP-SH:acetate ligase;
            HS-acyl-carrier protein:acetate ligase;
            [acyl-carrier protein]:acetate ligase;
            MadH
CLASS       Ligases;
            Forming carbon-sulfur bonds;
            Acid-thiol ligases
SYSNAME     acetate:[acyl-carrier-protein] ligase (AMP-forming)
REACTION    ATP + acetate + an [acyl-carrier protein] = AMP + diphosphate + an acetyl-[acyl-carrier protein] [RN:R09475]
ALL_REAC    R09475
SUBSTRATE   ATP [CPD:C00002];
            acetate [CPD:C00033];
            [acyl-carrier protein] [CPD:C00229]
PRODUCT     AMP [CPD:C00020];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013];
            acetyl-[acyl-carrier protein] [CPD:C03939]
COMMENT     This enzyme, from the anaerobic bacterium Malonomonas rubra, is a component of the multienzyme complex EC 4.1.1.89, biotin-dependent malonate decarboxylase. The enzyme uses the energy from hydrolysis of ATP to convert the thiol group of the acyl-carrier-protein-bound 2'-(5-phosphoribosyl)-3'-dephospho-CoA prosthetic group into its acetyl thioester [2].
